General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (r) Deemed Approval. – Any failure by an insurer or its URO to comply with the
2 deadlines and other requirements specified in this section will result in any healthcare services
3 subject to review to be automatically deemed authorized by the insurer."
4 SECTION 1.(b) Article 3 of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes is amended by
5 adding a new section to read:
6 "§ 58-3-500. Reports due regarding health benefit plans.
7 (a) Health Benefit Plan Reporting Requirements. – All insurers offering health benefits
8 shall be required to provide the following information to the Commissioner no later than March
9 1 of each year:
10 (1) Utilization review. – At a minimum, and subject to any rules adopted by the
11 Commissioner, insurers shall provide information regarding utilization review
12 approvals and noncertifications for the previous calendar year, reported
13 separately for medications and procedural codes, for all of the following:
14 a. The total number of medications and procedural codes subject to
15 utilization review, and specifically prior authorization.
16 b. The percentage of medications and procedural codes requiring prior
17 authorization.
18 c. The reasons for any noncertifications issued.
19 d. The number and percentage of utilization review determinations that
20 are appealed and the number and percentage of appeals that are
21 approved or denied at each stage of the appeal process.
22 e. The average time and distribution by percentile of number of days
23 between submission and response of each stage of the appeal process.
24 f. The number and percentage of providers who qualify for an exemption
25 from the utilization review process under this section.
26 (2) Reserved for future codification purposes.
27 (b) Commissioner Authority Over Required Information. – The Commissioner is
28 authorized to adopt rules related to this section. By rule, the Commissioner is authorized to
29 require additional information related to the subject of the required report. By rule, the
30 Commissioner is authorized to clarify or define further any information required under this
31 section to be the subject of a report.
32 (c) Commissioner Reporting Requirements. – No later than April 1 of each year, the
33 Commissioner shall compile the information received under subsection (a) of this section and
34 submit a report containing that compiled information to the Joint Legislative Commission on
35 Governmental Operations.
36 (d) Notwithstanding the penalty limits under G.S. 58-2-70, the failure of an insurer to
37 provide information required under this section is a violation subject to a fine of five thousand
38 dollars ($5,000) per day that the information is not provided."
39 SECTION 1.(c) In accordance with G.S. 135-48.24(b) and G.S. 135-48.30(a)(7),
40 which require the State Treasurer to implement procedures that are substantially similar to the
41 provisions of G.S. 58-50-61 for the North Carolina State Health Plan for Teachers and State
42 Employees (State Health Plan), the State Treasurer and the Executive Administrator of the State
43 Health Plan shall review all practices of the State Health Plan and all contracts with, and practices
44 of, any third party conducting any utilization review on behalf of the State Health Plan to ensure
45 compliance with subsection (a) of this section no later than the start of the next plan year.
46 SECTION 1.(d) Subsections (a) and (b) of this section become effective October 1,
47 2025, and apply to insurance contracts issued, renewed, or amended on or after that date.
